uno.collections.stacks

Interface Stack<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of an individual item stored in the Stack.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    UnboundedStack

    public interface Stack<E>
    This interface specifies the Stack abstract data type with standard stack operations.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      boolean isEmpty()
      Check if the stack is empty.
      E peek()
      Retrieve the element at the top of the stack without removing it.
      E pop()
      Remove the top element from this stack and return it.

    • Method Detail

      • isEmpty

        boolean isEmpty()
        Check if the stack is empty.
        Returns:
        true if the stack contains no items, false otherwise.

      • size

        int size()
        Retrieves the number of elements currently stored in the stack.
        Returns:
        The number of items stored.

      • peek

        E peek()
        Retrieve the element at the top of the stack without removing it.
        Returns:
        The top element.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - when the stack is empty.

      • pop

        E pop()
        Remove the top element from this stack and return it.
        Returns:
        The previous top element.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - when the stack is empty.

      • push

        E push(E item)
        Add an item to the top of this stack and return the new top.
        Parameters:
        item - The value to be added to the stack.
        Returns:
        The new top element on the stack.

      • search

        int search(java.lang.Object o)
        Determine the position of an item on the stack. Returns a 1-based position value, with the item of the top corresponding to the value 1. In essence, this tells you the number of pop operations that would have to be taken to remove the object from the stack.
        Parameters:
        o - The item to search for in the stack.
        Returns:
        A number greater than or equal to one if found, -1 if the item is not present.
